obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (7202)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7202&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Civil Defence Act, 1968.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends^1`
  line `to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in a State or part thereof on such date^2`
  line `, not being a date earlier than the`
  line `date of the expiry of the Defence of India Act, 1962 (51 of 1962), as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different States or different parts thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st October, 1975, vide notification No. S.O.478(E),dated 8th September, 1975, extended and brought into force in the State of`
  line Sikkim.
  line
  line `2. 10th July, 1968, vide notification No. S.O.2435(E), dated 5th July, 1968, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (7203)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7203&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "civil defence" includes any measures, not amounting to actual combat, for affording`
  line `protection to any person, property, place or thing in India or any part of the territory thereof against`
  line `any hostile attack, whether from air, land, sea or other places, or, for depriving any such attack`
  line `of the whole or part of its effect, whether such measures are taken before, during, at or after the time`
  line `of such attack^2`
  line `[or any measure taken for the purpose of disaster management, before, during, at, or`
  line `after any disaster];`
  line
  line `(b) "Civil Defence" Corps means the Corps formed wholly or mainly to meet the needs of civil`
  line `defence and includes an organisation deemed to be a Corps under the proviso to sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) "hostile attack" means any attack by any person or body of persons, whether during any war,`
  line `external aggression, internal disturbance or otherwise which endangers the security of any life,`
  line `property, place or thing in India or any part of the territory thereof;`
  line
  line `(d)"notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(e) "personal service injury" has the meaning assigned to it in the Personal Injuries (Emergency`
  line `Provisions) Act, 1962 (59 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(f) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator of the Union`
  line territory;
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(g) "disaster" means a disaster as defined in clause (d) of section 2 of the Disaster Management`
  line `Act, 2005(53 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(h) "disaster management" means the disaster management as defined in clause (e) of section 2 of`
  line `the Disaster Management Act, 2005(53 of 2005).]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st October, 1975, vide notification No. S.O.478(E),dated 8th September, 1975, extended and brought into force in the State of`
  line Sikkim
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-1-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (7204)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to make rules for civil defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7204&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, for securing civil`
  line `defence, by notification, make rules providing for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) preventing the prosecution of any work likely to prejudice civil defence;`
  line
  line `(b) instruction of members of the public regarding civil defence and their equipment for the`
  line `purposes of such defence;`
  line
  line `(c) provision, storage and maintenance of commodities and things required for civil defence;`
  line
  line `(d) prohibiting or regulating traffic, and the use of vessels, buoys, lights and signals in ports and`
  line `territorial, tidal and inland waters;`
  line
  line `(e) control of lights and sounds;`
  line
  line `(f) protection of life and property by taking fire prevention and other measures;`
  line
  line `(g) securing of any buildings, premises or other structures from being readily recognisable in the`
  line `event of a hostile attack;`
  line
  line `(h) for the prevention of danger to life or property, the demolition, destruction or rendering`
  line `useless, of any building, premises or other structures or any other property;`
  line
  line `(i) prohibiting or regulating the possession, use or disposal of—`
  line
  line `(i) explosives, inflammable substances, corrosive and other dangerous substances or articles,`
  line `arms and ammunition;`
  line
  line `(ii) vessels;`
  line
  line `(iii) wireless telegraphic apparatus;`
  line
  line `(iv) aircraft; and`
  line
  line `(v) photographic and signalling apparatus and any means of recording information;`
  line
  line `(j) evacuation of areas and the removal of property or animals therefrom;`
  line
  line `(k) accommodation in any area of persons evacuated from another area and the regulation of the`
  line `conduct of evacuated persons accommodated in such area;`
  line
  line `(l) billeting of evacuated person or persons authorised to perform functions under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) salvage of damaged buildings, structures and property and disposal of the dead;`
  line
  line `(n) seizure and custody or destruction of injured, unclaimed or dangerous animals;`
  line
  line `(o) ensuring the safety of—`
  line
  line `(i) ports, dockyards, lighthouses, lightships, aerodromes and facilities associated with aerial`
  line navigation;
  line
  line `(ii) railways, tramways, roads, bridges, canals and all other means of transport by land or`
  line water;
  line
  line `(iii) telegraphs, post offices, signalling apparatus and all other means of communication;`
  line
  line `(iv) sources and systems of water supply, works for the supply of water, gas or electricity and`
  line `all other works for public purposes;`
  line
  line `(v) vessels, aircraft, transport vehicles as defined in the Motor Vehicles Act, 1939`
  line `(4 of 1939), and rolling stocks of railways and tramways;`
  line
  line `(vi) warehouses and all other places used or intended to be used for storage purposes;`
  line
  line `(vii) mines, oilfields, factories or industrial or commercial undertakings generally, or any`
  line `mine, oilfield, factory or industrial or commercial undertaking in particular;`
  line
  line `(viii) laboratories and institutions where scientific or technological research or training is`
  line `conducted or imparted;`
  line
  line `(ix) all works and structures being part of, or connected with, anything earlier mentioned in`
  line `this clause; and`
  line
  line `(x) any other place or thing used or intended to be used for the purposes of Government or a`
  line `local authority or a semi-Government or autonomous organisation, the protection of which is`
  line `considered necessary or expedient for securing civil defence;`
  line
  line `(p) control of any road or pathway, waterway, ferry or bridge, river, canal or other source of`
  line `water supply;`
  line
  line `(q) precautionary measures, which the Government or any department thereof or any local`
  line `authority, members of police force, fire brigade and members of any other service or authority`
  line `employed primarily for purposes other than civil defence purposes should be required to take within`
  line `their respective jurisdictions or with respect to any personnel employed by them;`
  line
  line `(r) preventing or controlling any use of uniforms, whether official or otherwise, or flags or`
  line `official decorations like medals, badges or other insignia or anything similar thereto, the wearing of`
  line `which is calculated to deceive or to prejudice civil defence;`
  line
  line `(s) precautions to be taken or action to be taken by persons or authorities with a view to`
  line `protecting or acquainting the general public or any members thereof against the dangers involved in`
  line `any apprehended hostile attack;`
  line
  line `(t) requiring the owner or occupier of any building, structure or premises to make or carry out`
  line `such arrangements as may be necessary for the purposes of detection and prevention of fire;`
  line
  line `(u) taking of specified measures for dealing with outbreaks of fire;`
  line
  line `(v) directing that, subject to any specified exemption, no person present in any specified area`
  line `shall, between such hours as may be specified, be out of doors except under the authority of a written`
  line `permit granted by a specified authority or person;`
  line
  line `(w) (i) prohibiting the printing and publication of any newspaper, news-sheet, book or other`
  line `document containing matters prejudicial to civil defence;`
  line
  line `(ii) demanding security from any press used for the purpose of printing or publishing, and`
  line `forfeiting the copies of, any newspaper, news-sheet, book or other document containing any of the`
  line `matters referred to in sub-clause (i);`
  line
  line `(x) regulating the conduct of persons in respect of areas the control of which is considered`
  line `necessary or expedient, and removal of persons from such areas;`
  line
  line `(y) requiring any person or class of persons to comply with any scheme of civil defence;`
  line
  line `(z) any other provision which may be necessary for the purposes of civil defence.`
  line
  line `(2) Any rule made under sub-section (1) may provide that orders with regard to the matters specified`
  line `therein may be made by the State Government.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `(3) Any rule made under sub-section (1) may provide that a contravention thereof or any order made`
  line `thereunder shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, and where the`
  line `contravention is a continuing one, with a further fine which may extend to fifty rupees for every day, after`
  line `the first, during which such contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `4. Subs. by Act 42 of 1971, s. 6 (during emergency and six months thereafter) (w.e.f.3-12-1971).`
  line `"(3) Any rule made under sub-section (1) may provide that a contravention thereof or any order made or direction`
  line `given thereunder shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (7205)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Civil Defence Corps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7205&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may constitute, for any area`
  line `within the State, a body of persons to be called the Civil Defence Corps (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `"Corps") and may appoint a person, not being, in its opinion, below the rank of a District Magistrate (to`
  line `be known as the "Controller") to command such Corps:`
  line
  line `Provided that if there is in existence in any area in a State, immediately before the commencement of`
  line `this Act in that area, an organisation which, in the opinion of the State Government, may be entrusted`
  line `with the functions of the Corps, the State Government may, instead of constituting a separate Corps for`
  line `such area, call upon that organisation to take over or discharge the functions of the Corps in that area, and`
  line `thereupon such organisation shall be deemed, for the purposes of this Act, to be the Corps for that area.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, for the purpose of co-ordinating the activities of the Controllers`
  line `within the State, appoint a Director of Civil Defence and every Controller shall comply with the`
  line `directions given by such Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (7206)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Appointment of members and officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7206&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint as members of`
  line `the Corps persons who are fit and willing to serve as such and the Controller may appoint any member so`
  line `appointed to such office or command in the Corps, as such member is, in the opinion of the Controller, fit`
  line `to hold.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person appointed to be a member of the Corps shall be given a certificate of membership in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (7207)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Dismissal of members of Civil Defence Corps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7207&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any member of the Corps fails or has`
  line `failed, in the opinion of the Controller, to discharge his duties as such member satisfactorily or is or has`
  line `been found guilty of any misconduct in the discharge of his duties as such member, the Controller may,`
  line `after an inquiry in which such member of the Corps has been given a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line `heard in respect of the charges against him, by an order, dismiss such member from the Corps.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Controller is of opinion that the continued presence of any member of the Corps is`
  line `undesirable, he may, without assigning any reason, summarily dismiss such member from the Corps.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (7208)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7208&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `A member of the Corps who is dismissed from the Corps under section 6 may prefer an`
  line `appeal to the State Government within thirty days from the date of such dismissal and that Government`
  line `may, on such appeal, confirm, modify or reverse the order made by the Controller or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (7209)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions of members of Civil Defence Corps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7209&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The members of the Corps shall perform`
  line `such functions in relation to the carrying out of measures for civil defence as may be assigned to them by`
  line `rules made under this Act or by any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government or the Controller may, by order, call out a member of the Corps for training`
  line `or for discharging such functions in relation to the carrying out of measures for civil defence as may be`
  line `specified in such order.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to such orders as the Central Government may make in this behalf, any member of the`
  line `Corps of any State may at any time be required, by order, to discharge functions in relation to civil`
  line `defence in any other State and shall while discharging such functions, be deemed to be a member of the`
  line `Corps of that other State and be vested with the powers, functions and privileges and be subject to the`
  line `liabilities of a member of the Corps in that other State.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (7210)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7210&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make regulations`
  line `for carrying out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such regulations`
  line may—
  line
  line `(a) prescribe the functions of the members of the Corps and regulate the manner in which they`
  line `may be called out for service;`
  line
  line `(b) regulate the organisation, appointment, conditions of service, discipline, accoutrement and`
  line `clothing of members of any or all of the Corps;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the form of certificates of membership of any or all of the Corps`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (7211)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Provisions of the Personal Injuries (Emergency Provisions) Act to apply to injuries sustained by the members of the Corps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7211&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Personal Injuries (Emergency`
  line `Provisions) Act, 1962 (59 of 1962), and of every scheme made thereunder shall apply, so far as may be,`
  line `to every personal service injury sustained by any person appointed to be a member of the Corps as they`
  line `apply to personal service injury sustained by a civil defence volunteer, subject to the modifications that—`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to a civil defence volunteer under that Act or any scheme made thereunder shall`
  line `be construed as reference to a member of the Corps; and`
  line
  line `(b) any reference therein to the period of emergency shall, in relation to a member of the Corps,`
  line `be construed as the period during which this Act is in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (7212)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 42 of 1971, s. 6 (during emergency and six months thereafter) and restored thereafter (w.e.f. 3-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7212&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any member of the Corps on being called out by an order under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 8 neglects or refuses without sufficient excuse to obey such order or to discharge his functions`
  line `as such member or to obey any lawful order or direction given to him for the performance of his`
  line `functions, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, and where such`
  line `neglect or refusal is a continuing one, with a further fine which may extend to fifty rupees for every day,`
  line `after the first, during which such contravention continues.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `(2) If any person neglects or fails without any reasonable excuse to obey any order made or direction`
  line `given to him under this act or rules made thereunder, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend`
  line `to five hundred rupees, and where such negligence or failure is a continuing one, with a further fine which`
  line `may extend to fifty rupees for every day, after the first, during which such negligence or failure continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (7213)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Effect of Act and rules, etc., inconsistent with other enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7213&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this`
  line `Act or any rules thereunder or any order made under this Act or any such rule shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act or in any`
  line `instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appointment, order or rule made in relation to civil defence before the commencement of`
  line `this Act by or under any law relating to civil defence shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, continue to be in force until it is rescinded or altered under this Act, and be deemed`
  line `to have been made under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—"Commencement of this Act", in relation to any provision or area, means the`
  line `commencement of that provision or, as the case may be, the commencement of this Act in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (7214)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Ordinary avocations of life to be interfered with as little as possible.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7214&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any authority or`
  line `person acting in pursuance of this Act shall interfere with the ordinary avocations of life and the`
  line `enjoyment of property as little as may be consonant with the purpose of ensuring the public safety and`
  line `civil defence.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (7215)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Savings as to orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7215&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) No order made in exercise of any power conferred by or under this`
  line `Act shall be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order purports to have been made and signed by any authority in exercise of any power`
  line `conferred by or under this Act, a court shall, within the meaning of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(1 of 1872), presume that such order was so made by that authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (7216)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Act not to apply to measures taken for the protection of the Armed Forces.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7216&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line Nothing
  line `contained in this Act or any rule, regulation or order made thereunder shall apply to the Armed Forces of the Union or to any measures taken by any of the authorities in control of the Armed Forces of the Union`
  line `for the purpose of securing civil defence or safety of such forces or for the protection of any naval,`
  line `military or air force installations or stores.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (7217)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Limitation of prosecutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7217&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under this Act shall be`
  line `instituted against any person except by, or with the consent of, the Controller or any person authorised by`
  line `the Controller in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (7218)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of the Central Government to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1971, s. 6 (during emergency and six months thereafter) (w.e.f. 3-12-1971)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7218&sectionno=16A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Power of the Central Government to delegate.--The Central Government may, by order,`
  line `direct that any power or duty, which by this Act or any rule made thereunder is conferred or imposed`
  line `upon the Central Government shall, in such circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the direction, be exercised or discharged also by any officer or authority subordinate to the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b:
  sectionId (7219)
  sectionNo 16B
  orderNo 18
  title `Effect of order made by the Central Government, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1971, s. 6 (during emergency and six months thereafter) (w.e.f. 3-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7219&sectionno=16B&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[16B. Effect of order made by the Central Government, etc.--Any order made by the Central`
  line `Government or the officer or authority authorised by it under section 16A in relation to a matter to which`
  line `this Act or any rule made thereunder relates shall have effect, notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `order made by the State Government or any other authority with regard to such matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (7220)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7220&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, direct that—`
  line
  line `(a) all or any of the powers which may be exercised by it under this Act shall, in such`
  line `circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in that notification, be exercised`
  line `also by such officer, not being, in the opinion of the State Government, inferior in rank to that of a`
  line `District Magistrate, as may be specified in the said notification;`
  line
  line `(b) all or any of the powers which may be exercised by the Controller under this Act shall, in such`
  line `circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in that notification, be exercised`
  line `also by such officer, not being, in the opinion of the State Government, inferior in rank to that of a`
  line `Sub- Divisional Magistrate, as may be specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (7221)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7221&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Government, the Director or the Controller or any person, authorised by the`
  line `Government or the Controller, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this`
  line `Act or any rules or orders made thereunder or any orders issued under any such rule.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Government, the Director or the Controller`
  line `or any person, authorised by the Government or the Controller, for any damage caused or likely to be`
  line `caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or any rule made`
  line `thereunder or any order issued under any such rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (7222)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Authorised persons and members of the Corps to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1971, s. 6 (during emergency and six months thereafter) (w.e.f. 3-12-1971)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7222&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any person authorised`
  line `by^1[the Central Government] the Controller or the State Government under this Act and every member of`
  line `the Corps, while functioning as such, shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section`
  line `21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (7223)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412&sectionId=7223&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00004_196827_1517807319412
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made by`
  line `the Central Government under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or ^1`
  line `[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation, as the case may be, should not be made, the`
  line `rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
